
# 0x09-web_infrastructure_design


## What to learn
- DNS
- Monitoring
- Web Server
- Network basics
- Load balancer
- Server

| Tasks             | Description                                                                |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `0. Simple web stack` | On a whiteboard, design a one server web infrastructure that hosts the website that is reachable via www.foobar.com. Starts explanation by having a user wanting to access the website. |
| `1. Distributed web infrastructure`| On a whiteboard, design a three server web infrastructure that hosts the website www.foobar.com. |
| `2. Secured and monitored web infrastructure` | On a whiteboard, design a three server web infrastructure that hosts the website www.foobar.com, it must be secured, serve encrypted traffic, and be monitored. |
| `3. Scale up` | [Application server vs web server](https://intranet.alxswe.com/rltoken/toFi_SdFHyi2MaELB8ekqw) |

## Tech Stack

**Client:** DevOps, Sys Admin, web infrastructure

**VM(s):** Ubuntu 20.0.4, Ubuntu 14.04 - Python 3.4
